parameters.name: X-Fc-Account-Id
parameters.description: The ID of your Alibaba Cloud account.

parameters.name: X-Fc-Code-Checksum
parameters.description: The CRC-64 value of the function code package. This value is used to check data integrity. The value is automatically calculated by the tool.

parameters.name: X-Fc-Date
parameters.description: The time when the Function Compute is called. The format is **EEE,d MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss GMT**.

parameters.name: X-Fc-Log-Type
parameters.description:
The method used to return logs. Valid values:

*   **Tail**: returns the last 4 KB of logs that are generated for the current request.
*   **None**: No logs are returned for the current request. Default value: None.

parameters.name: X-Fc-Trace-Id
parameters.description: The trace ID of the invocation request of Function Compute.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of resources to return.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: The token required to obtain more results. If the number of resources exceeds the limit, the nextToken parameter is returned. You can include the parameter in subsequent calls to obtain more results. You do not need to provide this parameter in the first call.
